##China's first outbound tourism O2O bankruptcy liquidation, the impact of the outbreak of the shutdown of Tourism Road?

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to clear the fog, to seek the truth, to watch the Times.

In the long run, the tourism industry is still a sunrise industry

February 28, has been invested by Ali, known as "China's outbound Tourism O2o first share, " the 100-way travel network to start liquidation preparations.

The business, which relies on the visa business, has been struggling for the past few years, and the unexpected outbreak has been the last straw.

In essence, the entire tourism industry has suffered heavy losses as a result of the outbreak's impact. Li Xinjian, Dean of the Beijing International Studies University, said the direct loss to China's entire tourism industry during the 2020 Spring Festival is expected to be around 550 billion yuan. Wei Xiaoan, chief expert of the World Tourism Cities Federation, said China's total tourism revenue was 6.5 trillion yuan in 2019. Based on this estimate, the tourism industry lost 17.8 billion yuan when it stagnated for an average day.

In April 2016, Baicheng listed the new third board, becoming the first outbound O2O tourism share. As a bellwether company, as the first travel company to close down after the outbreak, will bctn be the first domino to fall? Under the ice, what is the way out for tourism?

Bankrupt visa magnate

According to public information, BCTN was founded in 2000, started as a tourist visa business, and later expanded as a tourist destination business. In March 2008, BCTN received a series of investments of 10 million US dollars from Fidelity Asia and UBS, it closed its nearly $20 million series B round in March 2014, led by Ali. New Third Board in June 2016 after sustained losses, has been removed in July 2019.

In the middle of 2018, the loss reached 12.8564 million yuan, a year-on-year decrease of 5.5273 million yuan. The company's financial report shows that the loss is mainly due to the fact that the company is still in the business expansion period in the internet industry, AND THE TECHNOLOGY R & D investment is at a relatively high level.

On February 28 this year, the company decided to start liquidation preparations, due to the impact of the new crown disease, capital can not maintain the company continued to operate. The company said it would carry out comprehensive aftercare and prepare its employees well in advance to fend for themselves.

In the view of the industry, the outbreak is just the last straw to overwhelm hundred Cheng.

In the past, traditional visa service providers could make good profits by taking advantage of information gaps due to the stringent entry and exit policies of the public and the complexity of applications. As more and more people become familiar with the visa process, in particular, many embassies and consulates have reduced the application materials, relaxed the application conditions, no doubt compressed the visa as a means of access and living space.

Zhang Yi, the founder and CEO of Ai Media Consulting, told China News weekly that the crisis at Bttn can not be solely attributed to the epidemic, as it is still losing money in a fast growing tourism industry, this shows or business management, business model problems.

"It's normal for companies to die out, " Liu Kejiang, director of beijing-based dehe Heng Law Firm, told China News weekly that a liquidation team should be set up according to law to clean up the company's assets, claims and debts, regardless of whether it is dissolved or bankrupt, handle the notice and announcement of creditors, deal with the remaining property after the company pays off its debts, etc. .

By definition, liquidation of an enterprise means that after the dissolution of the enterprise in accordance with its articles of association and the termination of its business operation due to bankruptcy or other reasons, the property, claims and debts of the enterprise shall be fully investigated and the claims shall be collected, economic activity involving the settlement of debts and the distribution of surplus property.

Regarding the bankruptcy liquidation of Baicheng travel network, Wang Zhuo, founder and CEO of Pincheng Travel, told China News weekly that this is a way of dealing with rational people who have a very clear idea and understand the operation of the company. Through this epidemic can be fully recognized, liquidation and registration, is a rational, legal, responsible business choice.

So, as a weather vane of the significance of the tourism industry, as the first announced after the outbreak of the closure of travel companies, travel network will be the first to be pulled down the "domino" it?

Industry insiders told China Newsweek that since tourism is not a heavy asset industry, its bankruptcy will not cause a big chain reaction, but to a certain extent it will speed up the consolidation of the industry, compared with some do not liquidate not bankrupt also do not operate the Zombie Enterprise, according to the liquidation orderly exit is a responsible action.

"there will certainly be a number of small and medium-sized platforms facing operational crisis, which is a normal survival of the fittest, " Zhang Yi said, adding that the tourism industry would experience explosive growth after the outbreak, which would be a good opportunity for businesses.

The tourism industry has been shut down

Hundred journey network bankruptcy liquidation behind, is the new crown pneumonia epidemic situation since the gradual collapse of the tourism industry.

On January 24, the Ministry of Culture and tourism issued an emergency notice asking travel agencies and online travel companies across the country to suspend group tours and "air ticket + Hotel" tours, travel agencies, tourist attractions, airlines, hotels and other businesses that had been looking forward to the peak of growth around the Lunar New Year holiday suddenly shut down. Since January 27, outbound travel has been suspended.

Online travel platforms such as CTRIP, flying pig and Qunar are also facing an unprecedented "refund" crisis, with companies saying they have paid more than 1 billion yuan for the refund.

The impact of the epidemic on the tourism industry has also spread from the asia-pacific region to the world. Fuji Jianzhuang, a time-honored Hotel in Aichi Prefecture, Japan, declared bankruptcy in mid-february, and Hamburg China Tours Co. , Ltd. filed an application for bankruptcy protection with the Hamburg court on February 21, the Indian Unicorn Oyo, dubbed the "Hotel Pinduoduo" , has announced it will cut about 5,000 jobs worldwide after Japan's Kobe night light cruise company filed for bankruptcy on March 2

The number of international visitors to the United States will fall 6 percent in the next three months, the biggest drop in international arrivals since the 2008 financial crisis, the American Travel Association predicted on March 3.

Global Online travel giant Booking Holdings forecast a 5%-10% decline in room bookings, a 10%-15% decline in total travel bookings and a 3%-7% decline in revenue in its first-quarter guidance. Greater China is now the hardest hit, as is the asia-pacific region, where bookings in Europe also fell a few days after the new coronavirus appeared in Italy.

Under the ice, what is the way out for tourism?

CTRIP's Chairman of the Board told the media that in the short term, international business will still be cancelled or revised, so in the short term, more emphasis will be placed on domestic travel.

"The outbound travel market is still relatively pessimistic, and this demand will gradually be transformed into a process that focuses on domestic travel, from near to far, " Dunning, deputy dean of the Beijing International Studies University, told China Newsweek, "Peripheral tour" is expected to start warming up first, people often do not go to large cities, traditional popular tourist destinations to gather, but will prefer a suitable climate, the better conditions during the epidemic. Compared with the traditional sense with the group tour, more people will choose small group, scattered spell.

Shanxi securities believes that the spread of the epidemic by the departments of policy tightening and consumer tourism confidence damaged, the recovery of the outbound tourism market still needs time. And in the long run, the tourism industry is still a sunrise industry, will not block the development of the industry due to the Black Swan crisis.

In order to help the industry through the winter, a series of security and incentive policies have also been introduced. On February 5, the Ministry of Culture and Tourism decided to temporarily refund to travel agencies 80 percent of the amount of the deposit for the quality of Tourism Services. The scope of the refund is to travel agencies that have already paid the deposit and received a travel agency business license in accordance with the law.

As of February 25,35,200 of the 39,000 travel agencies across the country had offered to return the bonds, with a total amount of 8 billion yuan due, and 3.462 billion yuan has been returned, said Liu Kezhi, director of the Marketing Management Department of the Ministry of Culture and tourism, on February 26.

At the local level, the Shanghai Municipal Bureau of Culture and tourism issued a notice on the resumption of some business activities of tourism enterprises in this city on March 14, conveying the good news of the resumption of work and production to travel agencies throughout the city, in addition to not operating inter-provincial (regional, municipal) and inbound and outbound group tourism business and "air ticket + hotel" tourism business, other business activities can be carried out normally.

In addition, the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation proposed that the maximum carrying period for losses incurred in 2020 by four major categories of difficult industries, such as tourism, would be extended from five years to eight years, and the China Tourism Association would exempt 212 member organizations from membership fees for 2020.

Dai Bin, President of the China Tourism Research Institute, said recently at the "headwind flying, the Jedi rebounding" summit of the Wenlu Revitalization Public Welfare Online conference that the tourism war epidemic in 2020 has been "stopped organizing tours, closed scenic spots, epidemic prevention" and "relying on the bottom line to save enterprises" , into A "strict prevention and control, orderly resumption of work, " the new stage.

"fragile industries need resilient growth, " Li told China's Newsweek. "resilient growth is not just about beating the cockroach, it's about being a sustainable mechanism. We should not "forget the pain" but learn from our mistakes. " Keep Building Moats; instead of trying to cope with uncertain environments, build the ability to be certain in advance. "If the tourism industry is still looking down the road after this storm, it may only see mud, and if it does not forget to look up at the sky, it may see a beautiful rainbow. "
